Articles.Content:
In my modded game I have lost the stock Squad rocket parts but have them in the un-modded version.

How can I find what mod is overwriting them?
Did you accidentally delete the folder? In your GameData folder there should be a folder called Squad. If it is gone, you can simply copy paste it from your un-modded version.
Do you have Janitor's Closet installed?  If so, did you hide the Squad parts in the mod filter?

JasOn thanks for the response.  

The Squad folder is complete and in tact.

linuxgurugamer, Thanks for the response and Thank you for all your hard work.  I very much enjoy and use many of your mods.

I do not have the Janitor's Closet installed but what is the MOD Filter file called?

On 4/2/2017 at 3:26 PM, DCH01 said:

linuxgurugamer, Thanks for the response and Thank you for all your hard work.  I very much enjoy and use many of your mods.

I do not have the Janitor's Closet installed but what is the MOD Filter file called?

The mod filter is a feature of Janitor's Closet. Can you post a screenshot of your GameData Folder?

Do you have SSTU installed? It hides some parts, if I remember correctly, by the way of custom patch files in the mod's folder. Also Ven's Stock Overhaul makes some parts look very different so you might think they're not there if you try to locate them visually.

Edited April 4, 2017 by Kerbital
